Description: PULS Kernel/GRUB Manager
 A powerful tool for Linux users who need fine-grained control over their
 system's kernel and boot process. Simplifies fetching, compiling, and
 installing mainline kernels while ensuring system safety through snapshots
 and Secure Boot management.
 .
 Features:
  - Mainline kernel fetching from kernel.org with GPG verification
  - Tailored compilation using localmodconfig
  - Automatic DKMS rebuild for modules (e.g. NVIDIA drivers)
  - GRUB parameter tuning and boot order management
  - Timestamped GRUB config backups with dry-run validation
  - Integrated Timeshift snapshot support
  - Machine Owner Key (MOK) management for Secure Boot
  - Kernel panic log analysis from pstore and kdump
  - Dashboard overview with system status
